(42, 12, 56, 40, 16, 3, 3, 'ye hypocrites, ye can discern the face of the sky', 'Connection of Hypocrisy and Discernment', 'Both passages emphasize the inability of hypocrites to discern the signs of the times, despite their ability to interpret natural signs. This highlights a theme of spiritual blindness in recognizing significant moments.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 56, 40, 11, 25, 25, 'discern this time', 'Discernment and Revelation', 'This connection highlights the theme of discernment in both passages. Luke emphasizes the inability to recognize the present time, while Matthew contrasts the wise with those who receive revelation as ''babes.''', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 56, 13, 12, 32, 32, NULL, 'Understanding of the Times', 'This connection highlights the theme of discernment regarding the times. Both passages emphasize the importance of recognizing the current situation and understanding what actions to take.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 56, 42, 19, 42, 44, 'this time', 'Connection of Discernment and Timing', 'Both passages emphasize the failure to discern the significance of the present time. In Luke 12:56, the inability to recognize ''this time'' parallels the lament in Luke 19:42 about not knowing ''this thy day.''', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 56, 27, 9, 24, 26, 'discern this time', 'Discernment of Prophetic Times', 'This connection highlights the theme of discernment regarding prophetic times. Luke''s call to recognize ''this time'' aligns with Daniel''s prophecy about the coming of the Messiah, emphasizing the importance of understanding the appointed periods.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 56, 39, 4, 2, 2, 'discern this time', 'Connection of Discernment and Righteousness', 'This connection highlights the theme of discernment regarding spiritual truths. In Luke, the call to recognize ''this time'' parallels the promise in Malachi of the ''Sun of righteousness'' bringing healing, suggesting a need for awareness of divine intervention.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 56, 48, 4, 4, 4, 'discern this time', 'Discernment of Time', 'This connection highlights the theme of recognizing significant moments in time. Luke emphasizes the failure to discern the present time, while Galatians marks the arrival of God''s Son at the appointed time.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 57, 5, 32, 29, 29, 'judge ye not what is right', 'Judgment and Understanding Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of discernment in both passages. Luke 12:57 asks why individuals do not judge what is right, while Deuteronomy 32:29 expresses a desire for wisdom and understanding regarding one''s future.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 57, 43, 7, 24, 24, 'judge ye not what is right', 'Judgment and Righteousness', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of making sound judgments. Luke 12:57 questions the ability to discern what is right, while John 7:24 instructs to judge with righteousness rather than appearance.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 57, 44, 2, 40, 40, 'judge ye not what is right', 'Judgment and Salvation Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of personal responsibility in discerning right from wrong. Both passages emphasize the need for individuals to take action in their spiritual lives, whether by judging what is right or saving themselves from an untoward generation.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 57, 44, 13, 26, 38, 'judge ye not what is right', 'Judgment and Recognition of Truth', 'This connection highlights the theme of recognizing what is right and true. In Luke, the call to judge rightly parallels the acknowledgment of Jesus'' true identity and the fulfillment of prophecy in Acts.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 57, 46, 11, 14, 14, 'judge ye not what is right', 'Judgment and Natural Order', 'This connection highlights the theme of discernment in both passages. Luke emphasizes the importance of judging what is right, while 1 Corinthians appeals to nature as a guide for understanding shame in appearance.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 57, 40, 21, 32, 32, 'judge ye not what is right', 'Judgment and Righteousness', 'This connection highlights the theme of judgment and righteousness. In Luke, the call to judge what is right relates to the response to John in Matthew, where the publicans and harlots recognized righteousness while others did not.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 57, 42, 21, 30, 30, 'judge ye not what is right', 'Judgment and Awareness of Time', 'This connection highlights the theme of self-awareness in discerning the rightness of actions and recognizing signs of the times. Both passages emphasize the necessity of personal judgment in understanding circumstances.', 'theme', 0.307, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 58, 20, 25, 8, 9, 'adversary to the magistrate', 'Conflict Resolution and Legal Proceedings', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of resolving disputes before they escalate to formal judgment. Luke advises diligence in dealing with an adversary to avoid imprisonment, while Proverbs cautions against hasty conflict and encourages direct dialogue with one''s neighbor.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 58, 40, 5, 23, 26, NULL, 'Adversary and Reconciliation Theme', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of reconciling with one''s adversary before facing judgment. They highlight the consequences of failing to do so, specifically the risk of being cast into prison. This connection underscores the urgency of resolving conflicts promptly.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 58, 18, 22, 21, 21, NULL, 'Peace and Deliverance Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of seeking peace and deliverance from adversaries. In Luke, the emphasis is on resolving disputes to avoid dire consequences, while Job encourages acquaintance with God for peace and good outcomes.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 58, 20, 6, 1, 5, NULL, 'Deliverance from Adversaries', 'Both passages emphasize the urgency of seeking deliverance from adversaries. In Luke, the focus is on avoiding imprisonment by reconciling with an adversary, while Proverbs advises prompt action to free oneself from obligations to a friend.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 58, 23, 55, 6, 6, NULL, 'Seeking Resolution and Deliverance', 'This connection highlights the urgency of seeking resolution before facing judgment. Both passages emphasize the importance of acting promptly to avoid dire consequences.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 58, 40, 18, 30, 30, 'cast thee into prison', 'Prison and Debt Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the consequence of failing to resolve disputes. Luke warns about being cast into prison due to unresolved issues with an adversary, while Matthew illustrates a scenario where a debtor is imprisoned for non-payment.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 58, 42, 13, 24, 28, 'give diligence that thou mayest be delivered', 'Striving for Deliverance', 'This connection highlights the theme of striving for deliverance from adversaries, whether in a legal context or in seeking entry into the kingdom of God. Both passages emphasize the urgency of making efforts to avoid dire consequences.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 59, 41, 12, 42, 42, 'the very last mite', 'Connection of Mites in Scripture', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of ''mites'' as a measure of value. In Luke, the reference to paying ''the very last mite'' connects to the widow''s offering of ''two mites'' in Mark, highlighting the significance of small contributions.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 59, 40, 18, 34, 34, NULL, 'Consequences of Unpaid Debt', 'Both passages emphasize the necessity of paying debts. Luke 12:59 speaks of paying ''the very last mite,'' while Matthew 18:34 mentions being delivered to tormentors until all is paid.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 59, 40, 25, 41, 41, NULL, 'Consequences of Judgment', 'This connection highlights the theme of judgment and consequences in both passages. Luke 12:59 speaks of paying debts, while Matthew 25:41 discusses being cast away for one''s actions.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 59, 42, 16, 26, 26, 'thou shalt not depart thence', 'Consequences of Unresolved Debt', 'This connection highlights the theme of accountability and the consequences of one''s actions. In both passages, there is an emphasis on the necessity of addressing debts, whether spiritual or moral, before one can move on to a different state of existence.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 59, 53, 1, 3, 3, 'thou shalt not depart thence', 'Faith and Accountability Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of accountability in faith. In Luke 12:59, the emphasis on paying debts relates to the growth of faith and charity in 2 Thessalonians 1:3, suggesting that both passages address the importance of responsibility in spiritual matters.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 13, 1, 60, 4, 17, 18, 'whose blood Pilate had mingled', 'Judgment and Righteousness Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of judgment and its implications for both the righteous and the ungodly. In Luke 13:1, the mention of bloodshed serves as a precursor to the discussion of judgment in 1 Peter 4:17-18, emphasizing the seriousness of divine accountability.', 'theme', 0.349, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 13, 1, 25, 2, 20, 20, 'whose blood Pilate had mingled', 'Violence Against Innocents', 'This connection highlights the theme of violence against innocents, as both passages reference the shedding of blood and the suffering of vulnerable individuals. In Luke, the Galileans are killed, while Lamentations mourns the deaths of priests and children.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
